      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "POWER UP NZ (3) made it two wins from his last three appearances two weeks ago, getting home by 13 metres over 2090m at this track when sent out as the $2.30 favourite. Likely to get all the favours from this nice draw. That latest effort is good enough to take out a race like this. IMPERIAL LAZ NZ (6) turned in an uncharacteristically poor run last start when 11 metres away in sixth over 2698m at Launceston. Form prior to that had been solid. Well placed and is sure to be there at the finish. COLBY SANZ (1) has to come into calculations on the back of some strong recent form, most recently when third at this track over 2090m after racing in behind the leader at the bell. Must be included. TOLD YOU TWICE (4) showed pleasing improvement last time out when third over 2200m at Launceston. Each-way claims.",
